cyclone.name: ETA
cyclone.current_location: about 250 miles WSW of Grand Cayman
cyclone.trajectory: moving ENE toward the Cayman Islands and central Cuba, then turning north toward the Florida Keys/south-Florida before bending northwest into the eastern Gulf of Mexico
cyclone.expected_landfall_location: Florida Keys or extreme south-Florida coast

weather_observation.watch_coast: Sebastian Inlet FL southward around the Florida peninsula to Bonita Beach, including Lake Okeechobee, the Florida Keys and Florida Bay; several Cuban provinces
weather_observation.warning_coast: Cayman Islands, central Cuba (Camaguey to Matanzas), north-western Bahamas
weather_observation.impacted_coast: Cuba, Florida Keys, south and central Florida peninsula, north-western Bahamas
weather_observation.wind: Only a 5% cumulative chance of tropical-storm-force (â‰¥34 kt) winds; strongest winds expected to remain well south of the Georgia coast.
weather_observation.storm_surge: None expected along the Georgia coast given current track well to the south and west.
weather_observation.rainfall: Outer moisture may bring intermittent showers early-to-mid week, but rainfall amounts likely remain below 2 inches at the port.
weather_observation.other_hazards: Enhanced rip currents and higher seas along the Georgia coast possible from long-period swells early next week.
